            <entry xml:id="entry_dys" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dys</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>dus</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>рукав</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>sleeve</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kærc... jæ ʽfcæggotæj zargæ kæny, jæ dystæj æmʒæǧd, jæ dymǵytæj
                            kafgæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>шуба своим воротником поет, рукавами отбивает такт, полами пляшет</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the fur coat sings with its collar, beats the beat with its sleeves,
                                dances with its flaps</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV
                            51</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*duš-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w>dauš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>плечо</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dōš</w>
                        <gloss><q>плечо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>dōš</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>dušä</w>
                        <gloss><q>рукав</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>daoš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>предплечье</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>плечо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>doṣ-</w>
                        <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>предплечье</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-nuristan"><lang/>
                        <w>dus</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>VII
                            90</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>VII
                                    90</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
                        <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned>. Сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w n="0" type="rec">духа</w></mentioned> в <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>пазуха</w></mentioned>. Перенос значения ‘часть тела’ → ‘часть одежды’
                    естествен; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ron"/> *‘поясница’ → ‘пояс’,
                    %idumæg%i ‘хвост’ → ‘пола’ [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_dymæg"
                            />].<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*duš-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w>dauš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>arm</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>shoulder</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dōš</w>
                        <gloss><q>shoulder</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>dōš</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/>
                        <w>dušä</w>
                        <gloss><q>sleeve</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>daoš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>forearm</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>shoulder</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>doṣ-</w>
                        <gloss><q>arm</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>forearm</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-nuristan"><lang/>
                        <w>dus</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                                    target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>VII
                            90</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_NTS"/><biblScope>VII
                                    90</biblScope></bibl>)</note>
                        <gloss><q>arm</q></gloss></mentioned>. Also here <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w type="rec">duxa</w></mentioned> in <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>pazukha</w></mentioned>. The transition of the meaning ‘part of the body’
                    → ‘part of the clothes’ is regular; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ron"/>
                    *‘loins’ → ‘belt’, %idumæg%i ‘tail’ → ‘flap’ [см. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_dymæg"/>].%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
